# Alembic — Database Migrations

Async migration environment for the FastAPI OWASP API Security Top 10 project.
Uses SQLModel metadata and an async SQLAlchemy engine (aiosqlite / asyncpg).

---

## Common Commands

### Generate a new migration (autogenerate from model changes)
```bash
uv run alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe your change"
```
> Always review the generated file in `alembic/versions/` before applying it.

### Apply all pending migrations
```bash
uv run alembic upgrade head
```

### Apply migrations up to a specific revision
```bash
uv run alembic upgrade <revision_id>
```

### Roll back the last migration
```bash
uv run alembic downgrade -1
```

### Roll back all migrations (reset to empty schema)
```bash
uv run alembic downgrade base
```

### Show current revision applied to the database
```bash
uv run alembic current
```

### Show full migration history
```bash
uv run alembic history --verbose
```

### Show pending migrations (not yet applied)
```bash
uv run alembic history -r current:head
```

---

## Notes

- Migrations are stored in `alembic/versions/`.
- The `env.py` file imports `app.persistence.models` to register all SQLModel tables
  with the metadata before autogenerate compares the schema.
- Never edit a migration file that has already been applied to a shared database.
  Create a new migration instead.
- The `alembic.ini` file must remain at the project root so the `alembic` CLI can
  find it when run from that directory.
